Amanda, may I have this dance?

958
01:12:30,340 --> 01:12:34,160
No. And if you want to get
arrested, just keep on talking.

959
01:12:34,795 --> 01:12:36,812
He's a horrible monster.

960
01:12:36,990 --> 01:12:38,645
I've got to tell her something.

961
01:12:38,818 --> 01:12:42,899
You'd better forget it for a while.
If you can't talk, you can't tell her.

962
01:12:51,716 --> 01:12:54,040
<i>Must you dance</i>

963
01:12:55,074 --> 01:12:57,589
<i>Every dance</i>

964
01:12:57,966 --> 01:13:03,316
<i>With the same fortunate man?</i>

965
01:13:03,485 --> 01:13:08,426
<i>You have danced with
him Since the music began</i>

966
01:13:09,867 --> 01:13:14,083
<i>Wort you change partners</i>

967
01:13:14,256 --> 01:13:16,545
<i>And dance with me?</i>

968
01:13:17,414 --> 01:13:19,601
<i>Must you dance</i>

969
01:13:20,206 --> 01:13:22,563
<i>Quite so close</i>

970
01:13:23,398 --> 01:13:28,544
<i>With your lips touching his face?</i>

971
01:13:29,215 --> 01:13:34,996
<i>Can't you see I'm
longing to be in his place</i>

972
01:13:35,332 --> 01:13:39,412
<i>Wort you change partners</i>

973
01:13:39,587 --> 01:13:42,046
<i>And dance with me?</i>

974
01:13:42,911 --> 01:13:47,956
<i>Ask him to sit this one
out And while you're alone</i>

975
01:13:49,227 --> 01:13:51,517
<i>I'll tell the waiter to tell him</i>

976
01:13:51,688 --> 01:13:56,132
<i>He's wanted on the telephone</i>

977
01:13:56,309 --> 01:13:58,531
<i>You've been locked</i>

978
01:13:59,134 --> 01:14:01,390
<i>In his arms</i>

979
01:14:02,092 --> 01:14:06,638
<i>Ever since heaven knows when</i>

980
01:14:06,813 --> 01:14:10,462
<i>Oh, won't you change partners</i>

981
01:14:10,637 --> 01:14:13,152
<i>And then</i>

982
01:14:13,329 --> 01:14:18,974
<i>You may never want To
change partners again</i>

983
01:14:19,512 --> 01:14:21,937
Would you mind if we went
outside for some fresh air?

984
01:14:22,105 --> 01:14:25,584
- It's awfully stuffy in here.
- Not at all, sweetheart.

985
01:14:34,406 --> 01:14:36,299
I'm sorry he upset you, dear.

986
01:14:36,466 --> 01:14:39,356
There's no reason we should
let him spoil our whole evening.

987
01:14:39,525 --> 01:14:41,281
I think he's contemptible.

988
01:14:41,453 --> 01:14:45,205
Oh, Amanda, don't say
that. Tony's all right.

989
01:14:45,708 --> 01:14:48,564
Except that he's a dirty,
double-crossing scientist.

990
01:14:48,734 --> 01:14:50,320
You're wanted on the telephone, sir.

991
01:14:50,495 --> 01:14:51,855
Just take the message, please.

992
01:14:52,024 --> 01:14:54,348
It's a long-distance call,
sir. Person-to-person.

993
01:14:54,518 --> 01:14:57,170
- Come along, Amanda.
- No, I'll meet you in the pavilion.

994
01:14:57,344 --> 01:14:59,066
I'll only be a moment.

995
01:15:11,804 --> 01:15:14,355
- Hello?
- Mr. Arden, long distance is calling.

996
01:15:14,530 --> 01:15:15,787
One moment, please.

997
01:15:15,960 --> 01:15:18,442
Go ahead with Honolulu, operator.

998
01:15:24,968 --> 01:15:26,986
This is Mr. Steve Arden, please?

999
01:15:27,163 --> 01:15:28,715
Yes, yes, who's this?

1000
01:15:28,892 --> 01:15:31,079
This is Miss Satsuma Naguchi, please.

1001
01:15:31,252 --> 01:15:34,369
- Who?
- Miss Satsuma Naguchi, please.

1002
01:15:34,543 --> 01:15:36,662
I would like information
about your marriage...

1003
01:15:36,836 --> 01:15:38,423
...to honorable lady Miss Cooper.

1004
01:15:38,599 --> 01:15:41,953
I am editor "Woman's
Column," Honolulu Daily Bugle.

1005
01:15:42,123 --> 01:15:43,947
Honolulu Daily what?

1006
01:15:44,117 --> 01:15:46,044
- Bugle.
- What?

1007
01:15:46,212 --> 01:15:48,002
Bugle, you know:

1008
01:15:52,694 --> 01:15:54,587
Amanda, may I speak to you, please?

1009
01:15:54,755 --> 01:15:57,871
- You certainly may not.
- But please, Amanda.

1010
01:17:51,273 --> 01:17:53,291
I'm awfully sorry, Miss Satsumi.

1011
01:17:53,467 --> 01:17:55,258
I don't understand
a word you're saying.

1012
01:17:55,429 --> 01:17:57,446
Not Miss Satsumi,
Miss Naguchi, please.

1013
01:17:57,623 --> 01:18:01,805
And if you do not understand, you
must be very stupid man, I think so.

1014
01:18:01,978 --> 01:18:04,562
I call you up like polite
lady to get simple information.

1015
01:18:05,136 --> 01:18:07,652
And now you make a big fuss
about nothing, I think so.

1016
01:18:07,829 --> 01:18:10,085
So I will commence with the beginning.

1017
01:18:10,255 --> 01:18:14,176
This is Miss Satsuma
Naguchi, Honolulu...

1018
01:18:23,952 --> 01:18:27,376
Amanda, I want you to repeat
after me everything I say.

1019
01:18:27,542 --> 01:18:29,060
Amanda, Amanda!

1020
01:18:29,238 --> 01:18:31,289
Dr. Flagg, stop that.
Stop that immediately.

1021
01:18:31,464 --> 01:18:34,853
Amanda. Amanda, wake up.

1022
01:18:38,679 --> 01:18:40,334
Oh, Stephen.

1023
01:18:55,200 --> 01:18:57,218
Hattie, have you ever been married?

1024
01:18:57,394 --> 01:19:00,352
- No, ma'am, but I've been engaged.
- Oh, just as good.

1025
01:19:00,520 --> 01:19:04,770
- No, ma'am, it's a lot better.
- Hattie.

1026
01:19:44,734 --> 01:19:47,692
I've opened the door for you five
times in the last 10 minutes...

1027
01:19:47,858 --> 01:19:50,409
...and Steve has caught me every time.

1028
01:19:50,617 --> 01:19:53,008
Come in through the window.
Don't let Joe see you.

1029
01:19:53,178 --> 01:19:55,297
He's issued a bench
warrant for your arrest.

1030
01:19:55,471 --> 01:19:59,654
And in case you don't know it, the
ceremony starts in five minutes.

1031
01:20:01,289 --> 01:20:03,873
- That doesn't give us much time.
- I guess it's too late.

1032
01:20:04,048 --> 01:20:06,599
After the trouble we had
getting you a marriage license?

1033
01:20:06,774 --> 01:20:09,460
But it's no good unless I can
get to her unconscious mind.

1034
01:20:09,633 --> 01:20:11,288
That'd take longer than five minutes.

1035
01:20:11,461 --> 01:20:13,546
I'd get her unconscious
in under five minutes.

1036
01:20:13,722 --> 01:20:16,374
I'd bust her in the jaw. I
guarantee she'd be unconscious.

1037
01:20:16,547 --> 01:20:17,804
Oh, don't be ridi...

1038
01:20:24,858 --> 01:20:26,615
Let's find that open window.

1039
01:20:41,746 --> 01:20:43,468
Oh, hello, Steve.

1040
01:20:43,641 --> 01:20:48,458
- We just came in through the window.
- Yeah, I guess we're in the wrong room.

1041
01:20:54,944 --> 01:20:56,496
Hi, kids.

1042
01:21:01,493 --> 01:21:03,317
Get out of here before I call Steve.

1043
01:21:03,487 --> 01:21:07,602
Amanda, darling, for what I'm
about to do, please forgive me.

1044
01:21:12,796 --> 01:21:14,756
Oh, I'm sorry, I just can't do it.

1045
01:21:14,923 --> 01:21:16,146
Hey, doc, duck!

1046
01:21:22,303 --> 01:21:23,697
Amanda, darling.

1047
01:21:23,866 --> 01:21:26,880
Hurry up, doc, get to her
unconscious before she comes to.

1048
01:21:27,323 --> 01:21:29,216
Repeat after me:

1049
01:21:29,384 --> 01:21:31,900
Tony loves Amanda.

1050
01:21:34,304 --> 01:21:37,228
Tony loves Amanda.

1051
01:21:51,291 --> 01:21:53,410
Stand up, Joe.

